76 * Actual message strings for each compiler message ID. There are currently

78 * individually):

80 * Data Table compiler

83 * NOTE1: These tables must match the enum list of message IDs in the file
84 * aslmessages.h exactly.
85 *
86 * NOTE2: With the introduction of the -vw option to disable specific messages,
87 * new messages should only be added to the end of this list, so that values
88 * for existing messages are not disturbed.
89 */

299/*******************************************************************************
300 *
301 * FUNCTION: AeDecodeMessageId
302 *
303 * PARAMETERS: MessageId - ASL message ID (exception code) to be
304 * formatted. Possibly fully encoded.
305 *
306 * RETURN: A string containing the exception message text.
307 *
308 * DESCRIPTION: This function validates and translates an ASL message ID into
309 * an ASCII string.
310 *
311 ******************************************************************************/
312
313const char *
314AeDecodeMessageId (
315 UINT16 MessageId)
316{
317 UINT32 Index;
318 const char **MessageTable;
319
320
321 /* Main ASL Compiler messages */
322
323 if (MessageId <= ASL_MSG_MAIN_COMPILER_END)
324 {
325 MessageTable = AslCompilerMsgs;
326 Index = MessageId;
327
328 if (Index >= ACPI_ARRAY_LENGTH (AslCompilerMsgs))
329 {
330 return ("[Unknown ASL Compiler exception ID]");
331 }
332 }
333
334 /* Data Table Compiler messages */
335
336 else if (MessageId <= ASL_MSG_TABLE_COMPILER_END)
337 {
338 MessageTable = AslTableCompilerMsgs;
339 Index = MessageId - ASL_MSG_TABLE_COMPILER;
340
341 if (Index >= ACPI_ARRAY_LENGTH (AslTableCompilerMsgs))
342 {
343 return ("[Unknown Table Compiler exception ID]");
344 }
345 }
346
347 /* Preprocessor messages */
348
349 else if (MessageId <= ASL_MSG_PREPROCESSOR_END)
350 {
351 MessageTable = AslPreprocessorMsgs;
352 Index = MessageId - ASL_MSG_PREPROCESSOR;
353
354 if (Index >= ACPI_ARRAY_LENGTH (AslPreprocessorMsgs))
355 {
356 return ("[Unknown Preprocessor exception ID]");
357 }
358 }
359
360 /* Everything else is unknown */
361
362 else
363 {
364 return ("[Unknown exception/component ID]");
365 }
366
367 return (MessageTable[Index]);
368}
369
370
371/*******************************************************************************
372 *
373 * FUNCTION: AeDecodeExceptionLevel
374 *
375 * PARAMETERS: Level - The ASL error level to be decoded
376 *
377 * RETURN: A string containing the error level text
378 *
379 * DESCRIPTION: This function validates and translates an ASL error level into
380 * an ASCII string.
381 *
382 ******************************************************************************/
383
384const char *
385AeDecodeExceptionLevel (
386 UINT8 Level)
387{
388 /* Range check on Level */
389
390 if (Level >= ACPI_ARRAY_LENGTH (AslErrorLevel))
391 {
392 return ("Unknown exception level");
393 }
394
395 /* Differentiate the string type to be used (IDE is all lower case) */
396
397 if (AslGbl_VerboseErrors)
398 {
399 return (AslErrorLevel[Level]);
400 }
401
402 return (AslErrorLevelIde[Level]);
403}
404
405
406/*******************************************************************************
407 *
408 * FUNCTION: AeBuildFullExceptionCode
409 *
410 * PARAMETERS: Level - ASL error level
411 * MessageId - ASL exception code to be formatted
412 *
413 * RETURN: Fully encoded exception code
414 *
415 * DESCRIPTION: Build the full exception code from the error level and the
416 * actual message ID.
417 *
418 ******************************************************************************/
419
420UINT16
421AeBuildFullExceptionCode (
422 UINT8 Level,
423 UINT16 MessageId)
424{
425
426 /*
427 * Error level is in the thousands slot (error/warning/remark, etc.)
428 * Error codes are 0 - 999
429 */
430 return (((Level + 1) * 1000) + MessageId);
431}
